@InProceedings{BHLR2007,
  author    = {Ayelet Butman and Danny Hermelin and Moshe Lewenstein and Dror Rawitz},
  title     = {Optimization Problems in Multiple-Interval Graphs},
  booktitle = {Proceedings of the 18th Annual ACM-SIAM Symposium on
               Discrete Algorithms (SODA'07)},  
  year      = 2007,
  comment   = {
To appear, SODA
Many applications of t-interval graphs:
 * MIS or MinVertCover for loss minimization,
 * MinDomSet for employees monitoring other employees in a store,
 * Clique for researcher who all need to speak together.
(2-1/t)-approx for Minimum Vertex Cover for t-interval graphs
t^2-approx for Minimum Dominating Set for t-interval graphs
Maximum Clique NP-complete for 3-interval graphs : Max-2DNF-SAT reduction:
  - one 3-interval for each litteral +xi and -xi:
    - interval A : unitary
    - intervals B & C : intersecting all other intervals B&C of litteral-3-intervals except -xi
  - one 3-interval for each clause:
    - intersecting every interval A of the +/-xi except the negation of litterals of the clause ->
    an interval with 2 holes = a 3-interval.
  -> a clique = all "valid" intervals and clauses
(t^2-t+1)/2-approx for clique on t-interval graphs   
  }
}

